'''microphone'''  (informal: ''[[mike]]'' or ''[[mic]]'')

# A device ([[transducer]]) used to [[convert]] [[sound wave]]s into a varying [[electric current]]; normally fed into an [[amplifier]] and either recorded or broadcast.

